topIssues.title: [Infra] Deploy Discord as AWS Service
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Deploy Discord plugin as a service in our AWS infrastructure that can handle incoming messages and route them to agents.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Discord service deployed to AWS
- [ ] Service can handle incoming Discord events
- [ ] Proper scaling and reliability
- [ ] Integrates with existing Cloud infrastructure

## Technical Notes

* We have a PR for this already
* Odilitime to help get Hanzla up to speed
* Needs to be a proper AWS service, not just local

## Assignee

Hanzla (with help from Odilitime)

## Priority

**P0 - This Week**

topIssues.title: [Agent] Create Universal Eliza Character File
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Design and implement the master character file for the default Eliza agent that will be cloned for each user. This is the "kitchen sink" agent with all capabilities.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Character file with appropriate personality (friendly, helpful, casual like Claudebot)
- [ ] Bio, topics, and tone defined
- [ ] System prompt optimized for assistant capabilities
- [ ] Message examples covering common use cases
- [ ] Personality is functional/utility-focused, not overly formal

## Technical Notes

* Reference Claudebot's lowercase, casual communication style
* Character should feel like "yo, what's up?" not corporate assistant
* Include personality traits that adapt to user interaction
* All plugins should be available to this character
* Must support dynamic plugin loading based on user requests

## Priority

**P0 - Day 3**

topIssues.title: [Research] Twilio SMS Regulatory Compliance
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Research Twilio SMS regulatory requirements and verify our existing account setup from the Trump project.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Verify existing Twilio account status
- [ ] Understand message volume limitations
- [ ] Check regulatory paperwork requirements
- [ ] Document any compliance steps needed for scale

## Technical Notes

**From today's meeting:**

* R Odili: "In my previous company that did Twilio with SMS, there was this big regulatory paper we had to fill out... I think that's going to take about a week"
* Shaw: "We did do this for the Trump thing and we got that set up"
* Question is can we send 50 or 50,000 messages?
* If limited to 50, need to talk to Twilio
* Shaw will escalate if Twilio breaks down
* Neo might know about the Trump project account
* Note: This is different from main Twilio that Ren has access to

## Priority

**P1 - Research in parallel, don't block development**

topIssues.title: [Milestone] Friday Demo - Talk to Eliza Agent
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Team alignment on Friday (Jan 31) demo milestone - ability to talk to Eliza agent through messaging platforms.

## Target State for Friday

Per Shaw: "Is there anything that would cause us to not feel confident about having something on Friday that we can talk to and start pushing?"

**Minimum viable demo:**

* Landing page that redirects to native messaging
* User can chat with Eliza agent through SMS/iMessage or Discord
* Basic end-to-end flow working

## Team Confidence Check (Jan 29 meeting)

| Team Member | Status | Concerns |
| -- | -- | -- |
| Rayan | Ready | Waiting on Sam's Twilio PR, Jasper for styling |
| Stan | Uncertain | "I don't know, to be honest... I'm not 100% sure" - will work hard |
| Ben | Cautious | "Want to confirm we can connect all the pieces" |
| Hanzla | Ready | Discord Gateway demo'd and working |
| Odili | Ready | Auto coding today, Friday realistic |
| Sam | In Progress | PR being reviewed by Ben |

## Key Dependencies

1. **Ben + Stan**: Need to connect and verify pieces work together
2. **Sam's Twilio PR**: Rayan blocked on this
3. [**Blue.io**](<http://Blue.io>)** testing**: Region locking research needed
4. **Jasper**: Background styling for landing page

## Fallback Strategy

Odili: "If we have a landing page where they can start talking to an agent... it doesn't have to be a product yet, but it's a good start/demo"

Shaw: Focus on [Blue.io](<http://Blue.io>) + onboarding first, Telegram as fallback

## Priority

**P0 - Friday Milestone**
